1
00:00:02,227 --> 00:00:04,359
In the previous episode...

2
00:00:05,047 --> 00:00:06,707
Team Nankatsu made it
to the finals

3
00:00:06,732 --> 00:00:08,469
of the single elimination
tournament in Shizuoka.

4
00:00:08,494 --> 00:00:09,648
Despite not being
able to count on

5
00:00:09,673 --> 00:00:11,195
their goalkeeper
Genzo Wakabayashi,

6
00:00:11,220 --> 00:00:12,695
they overcame that
and defeated team Shimada.

7
00:00:12,720 --> 00:00:13,977
A team known for

8
00:00:14,002 --> 00:00:15,952
their strong
defensive lineup.

9
00:00:15,977 --> 00:00:18,203
It was a difficult
battle for Team Nankatsu...

10
00:00:18,228 --> 00:00:19,388
Not only did they
have to deal with

11
00:00:22,812 --> 00:00:24,522
Shimada's
defensive prowess,

12
00:00:24,547 --> 00:00:26,182
but their endurance
and effectiveness

13
00:00:26,207 --> 00:00:28,247
was put to the test
due to the rain.

14
00:00:29,797 --> 00:00:30,797
During the second half,

15
00:00:30,822 --> 00:00:32,452
Tsubasa had
the determination

16
00:00:32,667 --> 00:00:34,667
not to let any of that
stop him.

17
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,000
And thanks to
his teammate's passes,

18
00:00:36,025 --> 00:00:37,211
he beat Shimada
to the punch

19
00:00:37,236 --> 00:00:39,076
and scored
the game winning goal.

20
00:00:40,862 --> 00:00:43,000
It was also then that
goalkeeper Yuzo Morisaki

21
00:00:43,025 --> 00:00:44,945
was able to show off
his skill and worth

22
00:00:44,970 --> 00:00:46,586
on the playing field.

23
00:00:48,770 --> 00:00:49,569
Stopping a shot

24
00:00:49,594 --> 00:00:51,085
could've cost
Nankatsu the game.

25
00:00:51,110 --> 00:00:52,280
On the other hand,

26
00:00:52,305 --> 00:00:54,803
team Meiwa also made it
to the finals...

27
00:00:54,828 --> 00:00:56,367
lead by the tiger himself,
Kojiro Hyuga.

28
00:01:00,578 --> 00:01:05,578
[opening theme]

29
00:02:43,529 --> 00:02:46,099
Episode 12:
Crushing Wakabayashi.

30
00:02:46,178 --> 00:02:48,928
Shimizu will win it all!
Shimizu will never fall!

31
00:02:49,048 --> 00:02:50,008
-Go team! Go team!
-Go team! Go team!

32
00:02:50,138 --> 00:02:50,888
-You're the one!
-You're the one!

33
00:02:51,008 --> 00:02:51,678
-Shimizu knows that
-Shimizu knows that

34
00:02:51,798 --> 00:02:52,638
-they are done!
-they are done!

35
00:02:52,758 --> 00:02:53,718
-Go team! Go team!
-There it is...

36
00:02:53,838 --> 00:02:54,798
-You're the one!
-Each team's crowd

37
00:02:54,928 --> 00:02:56,668
is going wild cheering.

38
00:02:56,693 --> 00:02:59,193
Finally, the moment has
come to decide which team

39
00:02:59,218 --> 00:03:01,758
will represent
the Shizuoka prefecture.

40
00:03:02,147 --> 00:03:03,523
Which team will win

41
00:03:03,548 --> 00:03:05,809
to compete at
the national tournament?

42
00:03:05,834 --> 00:03:06,983
Will it be team Nankatsu,

43
00:03:07,008 --> 00:03:07,528
mostly composed of team members from Shutetsu?

44
00:03:07,528 --> 00:03:09,588
mostly composed of team members from Shutetsu?
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC

45
00:03:09,588 --> 00:03:09,888
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC

46
00:03:09,888 --> 00:03:11,718
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC
Or will it be team Shimizu?

47
00:03:11,718 --> 00:03:11,838
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC

48
00:03:11,838 --> 00:03:13,008
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC
Whom have won perfect games

49
00:03:13,008 --> 00:03:13,138
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC

50
00:03:13,138 --> 00:03:14,798
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC
in all of their matches thus far.

51
00:03:14,798 --> 00:03:15,198
NATIONAL JUVENILE SOCCER TOURNAMENT SHIZUOKA TOURNAMENT NANKATSU SC

52
00:03:15,508 --> 00:03:17,718
Listen, the time has come, everyone.

53
00:03:18,208 --> 00:03:19,998
Hey, how's your leg doing, by the way?

54
00:03:20,023 --> 00:03:21,483
I feel like it's brand new.

55
00:03:21,508 --> 00:03:23,798
I wouldn't let you guys
play this match without me.

56
00:03:24,493 --> 00:03:25,613
Thanks again, Yuzo.

57
00:03:25,638 --> 00:03:26,968
You defended the goal
for us.

58
00:03:27,468 --> 00:03:28,678
-Job well done.
-Mhm.

59
00:03:29,548 --> 00:03:31,758
Now I'll be the one
protecting our team's goal

60
00:03:31,783 --> 00:03:33,193
with everything I've got.

61
00:03:33,388 --> 00:03:35,048
SHIMIZU FC LOCKER ROOM

62
00:03:35,048 --> 00:03:35,678
SHIMIZU FC LOCKER ROOM
Remember,

63
00:03:35,678 --> 00:03:35,838
Remember,

64
00:03:35,968 --> 00:03:38,388
our strategy is to cover
that kid Tsubasa Ozora

65
00:03:38,413 --> 00:03:39,413
at all costs.

66
00:03:39,774 --> 00:03:41,484
It doesn't matter
if he has the ball or not.

67
00:03:41,605 --> 00:03:44,421
I don't want you to let him
move freely whatsoever,

68
00:03:44,446 --> 00:03:45,621
you all got that?

69
00:03:45,676 --> 00:03:46,678
-Yes!
-Yes!

70
00:03:46,993 --> 00:03:48,873
I'll say this once.
Keep your eyes on him.

71
00:03:48,968 --> 00:03:50,678
-Yes.
-We'll do that, Captain.

72
00:03:50,838 --> 00:03:51,838
Mhm.

73
00:03:56,258 --> 00:03:57,523
Both teams
have put forth

74
00:03:57,548 --> 00:03:59,388
their best effort
to be here.

75
00:03:59,413 --> 00:04:00,463
It's the moment of truth.

76
00:04:00,758 --> 00:04:01,928
Now we'll finally see

77
00:04:01,953 --> 00:04:04,230
Nankatsu and Shimizu
face off.

78
00:04:04,255 --> 00:04:04,941
The team that wins

79
00:04:04,966 --> 00:04:07,006
will represent
Shizuoka prefecture.

80
00:04:07,678 --> 00:04:09,468
This sucks.
I'm on the bench again?

81
00:04:09,683 --> 00:04:12,045
You can do it, Tsubasa!

82
00:04:12,070 --> 00:04:13,150
You are the best!

83
00:04:13,175 --> 00:04:14,675
Hey, Sanae,
you're too intense.

84
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:15,870
The match
hasn't even started.

85
00:04:15,895 --> 00:04:17,305
Can you tone it down a tad?

86
00:04:17,523 --> 00:04:18,813
Who are you calling intense?

87
00:04:18,943 --> 00:04:21,153
Don't you know
how important this match is?

88
00:04:21,178 --> 00:04:22,838
Now more than ever,
we have to--

89
00:04:22,863 --> 00:04:24,483
Come on, Tsubasa,
score on them!

90
00:04:24,538 --> 00:04:25,748
What? What?

91
00:04:26,048 --> 00:04:29,298
I thought I heard someone
yelling out Tsubasa's name.

92
00:04:29,428 --> 00:04:31,138
You thought you were
his only fan?

93
00:04:31,258 --> 00:04:32,928
There's tons of girls
that cheer him.

94
00:04:33,048 --> 00:04:33,838
Listen carefully,

95
00:04:33,968 --> 00:04:36,548
I'm the only one who can
really cheer Tsubasa on.

96
00:04:37,508 --> 00:04:38,705
Both teams
are waiting on

97
00:04:38,730 --> 00:04:40,218
the ref's signal to begin.

98
00:04:40,636 --> 00:04:43,485
Nankatsu maintains
their 4-3-3 formation,

99
00:04:43,510 --> 00:04:46,850
lead by Tsubasa Ozora,
and Genzo Wakabayashi.

100
00:04:46,875 --> 00:04:48,808
Tsubasa scored a hat trick
in his last match,

101
00:04:48,833 --> 00:04:51,043
while Genzo was out
because of an injury.

102
00:04:51,068 --> 00:04:53,898
But today, he's ready to
jump out into the field.

103
00:04:53,923 --> 00:04:55,713
Nankatsu's roster
is complete.

104
00:04:56,678 --> 00:04:58,048
Team Shimizu
prefers to use

105
00:04:58,178 --> 00:04:59,718
a defensive formation
favorable to

106
00:04:59,838 --> 00:05:01,798
his team leader
Morimichi Kawakami,

107
00:05:01,823 --> 00:05:02,613
their prodigy.

108
00:05:02,838 --> 00:05:05,508
With a 4-4-2 formation,
they're a well-rounded team

109
00:05:05,508 --> 00:05:07,508
who doesn't fall short
to Nankatsu.

110
00:05:07,508 --> 00:05:09,258
Their players
are very strong.

111
00:05:09,638 --> 00:05:11,468
Both teams have
practically scored

112
00:05:11,493 --> 00:05:13,413
the same amount of goals
in their matches.

113
00:05:13,758 --> 00:05:15,548
Which makes it hard
to predict the winner

114
00:05:15,573 --> 00:05:18,399
of this nail-biting
encounter.

115
00:05:19,178 --> 00:05:21,588
If we win this, we'll go to
the national tournament.

116
00:05:22,088 --> 00:05:23,678
Hey, Tsubasa,
It's time to win.

117
00:05:23,968 --> 00:05:24,968
Yeah.

118
00:05:26,968 --> 00:05:28,258
And the official whistle

119
00:05:28,388 --> 00:05:30,718
sparks up the hearts
of these young men.

120
00:05:31,178 --> 00:05:33,076
Taro Misaki dribbles
the ball with determination.

121
00:05:34,088 --> 00:05:35,388
I won't let you go through.

122
00:05:35,508 --> 00:05:36,548
Here, Hajime!

123
00:05:36,798 --> 00:05:38,903
Taro Misaki
quickly changes the pace

124
00:05:38,928 --> 00:05:40,068
and passes to
Hajime Taki.

125
00:05:40,268 --> 00:05:41,268
Tsubasa!

126
00:05:41,293 --> 00:05:42,638
Tsubasa
makes a run for it,

127
00:05:42,663 --> 00:05:43,953
looking for a pass
from Hajime.

128
00:05:44,178 --> 00:05:45,718
-Oh!
-Oh!

129
00:05:45,838 --> 00:05:47,338
But Tsubasa finds himself

130
00:05:47,363 --> 00:05:48,903
totally covered
by two other players.

131
00:05:48,928 --> 00:05:49,928
Huh?!

132
00:05:50,258 --> 00:05:51,508
Be careful, Hajime!

133
00:05:51,638 --> 00:05:53,459
That ball's mine.

134
00:05:53,838 --> 00:05:54,838
And team Shimizu

135
00:05:54,968 --> 00:05:56,826
-just stole the ball.
-Run, Ichiro, move it!

136
00:05:57,138 --> 00:05:59,508
Now, the yellow team starts
their counterattack.

137
00:05:59,638 --> 00:06:00,678
Pass it, I'm open.

138
00:06:01,008 --> 00:06:02,840
Ichiro Kanda
is asking for the ball.

139
00:06:02,865 --> 00:06:04,235
Everyone, run back!

140
00:06:04,623 --> 00:06:05,373
Ichiro!

141
00:06:05,548 --> 00:06:07,218
Suzuki to Ichiro Kanda.

142
00:06:09,475 --> 00:06:10,849
I won't let you score.

143
00:06:12,209 --> 00:06:14,021
Ichiro Kanda
avoids that sliding tackle

144
00:06:14,046 --> 00:06:15,258
from Nankatsu.

145
00:06:15,493 --> 00:06:16,863
There's no doubt that
Shizimu's players

146
00:06:16,888 --> 00:06:17,758
are very capable.

147
00:06:17,783 --> 00:06:19,178
But are they good enough
to get through

148
00:06:19,203 --> 00:06:20,588
-Shingo Takasugi?
-Don't dream of it.

149
00:06:20,588 --> 00:06:21,758
Watch carefully
as Obayashi

150
00:06:21,783 --> 00:06:23,129
and Koji Murakami

151
00:06:23,154 --> 00:06:24,338
get close to
the penalty area.

152
00:06:24,468 --> 00:06:26,008
-Don't let them shoot.
-We have to block them.

153
00:06:27,508 --> 00:06:29,928
Ichiro Kanda
kicks a pass to Obayashi.

154
00:06:31,678 --> 00:06:32,678
Take this!

155
00:06:32,798 --> 00:06:34,693
Obayashi
shoots towards the goal...

156
00:06:34,718 --> 00:06:35,638
Captain!

157
00:06:35,758 --> 00:06:37,048
Look out, Genzo!

158
00:06:38,668 --> 00:06:39,613
The goalkeeper

159
00:06:39,638 --> 00:06:41,008
launches himself
towards the ball.

160
00:06:41,138 --> 00:06:43,508
Genzo Wakabayashi embraces
the impact of the shot.

161
00:06:44,001 --> 00:06:46,342
-No!
-Good job, Captain!

162
00:06:47,943 --> 00:06:49,903
It's mine.
Now it's our turn.

163
00:06:49,928 --> 00:06:50,928
Tsubasa!

164
00:06:51,388 --> 00:06:52,798
Genzo Wakabayashi

165
00:06:52,823 --> 00:06:54,693
sends the ball flying to
the other side of the field

166
00:06:54,718 --> 00:06:56,718
to Nankatsu's forward
Tsubasa Ozora.

167
00:06:56,743 --> 00:06:58,693
However,
there's a lot to overcome:

168
00:06:58,718 --> 00:06:59,968
two players from Shimizu.

169
00:07:00,388 --> 00:07:01,888
The three of
them jump at the same time,

170
00:07:02,008 --> 00:07:04,218
but the Nankatsu's
shining star

171
00:07:04,243 --> 00:07:06,588
gets the height needed to
keep possession of the ball.

172
00:07:08,508 --> 00:07:09,588
Taro Misaki receives it

173
00:07:09,613 --> 00:07:11,258
and passes
without thinking twice,

174
00:07:11,388 --> 00:07:13,338
back to Tsubasa whom
runs towards the goal.

175
00:07:15,718 --> 00:07:17,838
Tsubasa, you can do it!

176
00:07:19,873 --> 00:07:21,678
And there it is.

177
00:07:21,798 --> 00:07:24,548
Nankatsu's number ten's
shot is a fierce one.

178
00:07:24,973 --> 00:07:26,693
But the ball
hits the goal post

179
00:07:26,718 --> 00:07:27,508
with a direct impact.

180
00:07:27,638 --> 00:07:29,548
Oh! Hey, that should've
gone in.

181
00:07:29,588 --> 00:07:31,638
-That was too close.
-Too close for comfort.

182
00:07:35,588 --> 00:07:36,708
That wasn't enough guys.

183
00:07:36,733 --> 00:07:38,248
We need one more
to cover him.

184
00:07:38,273 --> 00:07:40,483
Aww, that shot should've
made it in.

185
00:07:40,508 --> 00:07:41,718
That's not fair.

186
00:07:41,718 --> 00:07:43,218
-It's okay, Tsubasa.
-Huh?

187
00:07:43,338 --> 00:07:44,548
Don't worry about it.

188
00:07:44,678 --> 00:07:46,508
You'll get to score a goal
next time.

189
00:07:47,038 --> 00:07:48,438
Who does she think
she is?

190
00:07:48,463 --> 00:07:51,838
Huh?
Hey, Sanae, wait up!

191
00:07:51,863 --> 00:07:53,403
-Tsubasa!
-Huh?

192
00:07:53,668 --> 00:07:54,828
Did you forget about me?

193
00:07:54,853 --> 00:07:56,903
It's me! Yayoi!

194
00:07:57,428 --> 00:07:59,048
I came to cheer you on.

195
00:07:59,592 --> 00:08:00,592
Uh...

196
00:08:03,138 --> 00:08:04,428
Hey, just wait a second!

197
00:08:04,548 --> 00:08:05,758
Oh! Huh?

198
00:08:05,993 --> 00:08:07,693
What's with you and Tsubasa?

199
00:08:07,718 --> 00:08:08,718
Who are you?

200
00:08:09,403 --> 00:08:11,443
Hello and who might you be?

201
00:08:11,468 --> 00:08:13,678
I'm the leader of
Nankatsu's cheering squad.

202
00:08:13,823 --> 00:08:16,403
And I also protect
Tsubasa from harpies.

203
00:08:16,428 --> 00:08:17,508
I can see that.

204
00:08:17,638 --> 00:08:19,506
Tsubasa and I used to
go to the same school.

205
00:08:19,531 --> 00:08:21,420
My name is Yayoi Aoba.

206
00:08:21,468 --> 00:08:22,468
Nice to meet you.

207
00:08:22,933 --> 00:08:24,283
Hey, cutie, how are you?

208
00:08:24,308 --> 00:08:25,740
I'm also a--

209
00:08:25,765 --> 00:08:28,053
You shut up, Koji.
Don't be a bootlicker.

210
00:08:28,763 --> 00:08:31,593
Tsubasa is incredible
when he plays, isn't he?

211
00:08:31,618 --> 00:08:33,008
He's got so much energy.

212
00:08:33,138 --> 00:08:34,826
Ah... Huh?

213
00:08:36,718 --> 00:08:38,428
I remember him
playing with his soccer ball

214
00:08:38,548 --> 00:08:39,758
at school all day long.

215
00:08:39,783 --> 00:08:40,983
He was never without it.

216
00:08:41,388 --> 00:08:42,968
While watching him play
in the field,

217
00:08:43,088 --> 00:08:44,920
I can tell that
his heart really...

218
00:08:45,548 --> 00:08:47,048
belongs to the field.

219
00:08:47,209 --> 00:08:49,178
He looks so much happier.

220
00:08:50,258 --> 00:08:52,298
Back then, everyone thought
that he was weird...

221
00:08:52,638 --> 00:08:54,508
because he spent his days
playing soccer.

222
00:08:54,929 --> 00:08:57,179
Doesn't he ever get tired
of playing with the ball?

223
00:08:57,823 --> 00:08:59,403
But I was fascinated with

224
00:08:59,428 --> 00:09:00,968
Tsubasa's passion
for soccer.

225
00:09:00,993 --> 00:09:01,823
He never got tired.

226
00:09:02,138 --> 00:09:04,468
Yayoi, we want to
leave already.

227
00:09:06,483 --> 00:09:07,483
It was sad.

228
00:09:07,508 --> 00:09:09,638
I never could tell him
how I felt for him.

229
00:09:09,678 --> 00:09:12,218
By the time I realized,
he had already left.

230
00:09:13,838 --> 00:09:15,388
Aren't you going to
cheer for him?

231
00:09:15,529 --> 00:09:17,483
Tsubasa has the ball now
and he's running.

232
00:09:17,508 --> 00:09:18,468
What?!

233
00:09:18,588 --> 00:09:21,138
The ball lands directly
on Tsubasa's chest.

234
00:09:22,528 --> 00:09:23,758
-Huh?
-But now there are

235
00:09:23,783 --> 00:09:25,718
three Shimizu players
covering him.

236
00:09:26,388 --> 00:09:27,548
Now, there's three players?

237
00:09:28,638 --> 00:09:29,678
You want three on him?

238
00:09:30,548 --> 00:09:31,218
Yes, exactly.

239
00:09:31,338 --> 00:09:33,468
But if we were to do that,
wouldn't our goal

240
00:09:33,493 --> 00:09:35,298
be totally defenseless,
Captain?

241
00:09:35,428 --> 00:09:36,588
You're overreacting.

242
00:09:37,063 --> 00:09:38,773
Even if he dares to shoot...

243
00:09:38,798 --> 00:09:41,088
I know that I can stop
his shot easily.

244
00:09:41,298 --> 00:09:42,588
That's my job here.

245
00:09:43,048 --> 00:09:45,560
He's the only scorer
Nankatsu's got.

246
00:09:46,239 --> 00:09:48,739
Which means if we cover
Tsubasa the whole time...

247
00:09:48,928 --> 00:09:50,968
there's no way they can
score on us.

248
00:09:52,662 --> 00:09:53,618
This is the first time

249
00:09:53,643 --> 00:09:56,483
Tsubasa's being covered
by three players at a time.

250
00:09:56,508 --> 00:09:57,758
How will he overcome
this strategy

251
00:09:57,783 --> 00:09:59,279
by Team Shimizu?

252
00:09:59,304 --> 00:10:00,594
